### Last Good Version

1.45

### First Bad Version

1.46, 1.47

### Steps to reproduce

After upgrading to Playwright 1.47 from 1.45, I discovered that the behavior of using a fixture accepting array of objects changed.

I have prepared a simplified example that illustrates this situation.

```
import { test as baseTest } from '@playwright/test';

const test = baseTest.extend<{
    array: any[];
}>({});

test.use({
    array: [{ foo: '1' }, { foo: '2' }],
});

test('Example test', ({ array }) => {
    console.log(array);
});
```

### Expected behavior

When running this code on Playwright 1.45 it prints:
`[ { foo: '1' }, { foo: '2' } ]`

### Actual behavior

When running this code on Playwright 1.46 it prints:
`{ foo: '1' }`

### Additional context

It used to work before, so it looks like a regression to me. When using e.g. array of numbers, it works as expected.

